Over on @realmoney I have tried over the last four stressful weeks to have a steady hand and transparent pen. Unlike most, nearly all my trades are memorialized in price - whether I lose, win or draw. (These days I lose far more often!) I have gotten aggressive on the long

side over the last few trading days. If you want to see what I am trading and investing go over to our site. My obligation is to @realmoney and not to Twitter where you see only a very small portion. I have been writing my blog for 23 years - so I suppose

I might be doing something right. I am now getting more bullish and I write 5k to 10k words a day on our site - explaining why, when and how and in what size I am buying or shorting. Again, you see the Cliff Notes only here..
Finally, unlike many I am not self confident in view, I take ownership to my mistakes and don't sweep my losers under the rug. I am often wrong and always in doubt. And I learn more every day.
